      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Scholar" href="/users/Draykoneyus">Draykoneyus</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Scholar">Scholar</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">314 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Decent  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">I know a lot of FFXI dragoons will be migrating to the lancer class in FFXIV for the love of the lance, but where are our little blue friends? I have hope that through a version update or expansion, lancer will gain the ability to &quot;rule over dragons&quot; as its predecessor did. The question is, how will the devs implement it?  <br /> <br />They cant just add another class because there would then be 2 spear/lance wielding classes. Given that the FFXIV job system allows you to sort of make your own class out of abilities from other classes, I was thinking maybe the addition of a dragon knight will come in the form of abilities. For example, what if there was a quest that gave you, as a reward, the &quot;call wyvern&quot; ability (or whatever they want to call it) and equipping it essentially just makes you a dragoon. Perhaps the quests could even be tiered like the AF quests were: quests 1-3 would give you different jump attacks, and the 4th gives call wyvern.  <br /> <br />Essentially what I'm getting at is advanced jobs or job upgrades through the form of quested abilities. The class wouldn't be different per se, just specialized. In fact, there could be multiple specialties for each class. I feel like there could be a lot of possibilities with something like this but maybe I'm being overzealous.   <br /> <br />Anyway, what do you guys think? Do any other Drg enthusiasts have any ideas of how we might see a Dragon Knight class? I want to hear them!      </div>
