      <div class="msgContentFrame">I think people are assuming a little too much to say that there will not be a way to make a dragoon type class in the future. That being said there really might not be, but given the popularity of the dragoon I think its more likely that they will fit it in some way or another. Dragoon had an almost cult-like following. Some people hated them, but others absolutely loved them (I'm one of the latter). <br /> <br />How they might do it is another story. I can see it as a quested ability of some sort like already mentioned, but another way is through a separate class that specializes in animal husbandry (I think someone on a different thread has suggested this before). The class would gather, capture, or raise animals (chocobos maybe!) for a number of reasons. The animals could produce items for cooking, or tanning just as an example. In combat they could charm animals like a BST could in FFXI to help fight. Once mastered you could carry that ability over to your Lancer (for example), train or tame your wyvern, and now you have a Dragoon type class. Granted that doesn't take care of the jump ability, but maybe that is an ability that might appear in the future for Lancers. I think this idea would be cool because you could have more freedom with your &quot;Dragoon&quot; in that if you wanted a sword wielding DRG you could (not me though I love the lance). If you were an avid WoW player and liked the hunter than you could combine the ability with the archer and have your hunter. </div>
      <div class="msgFtFrame">
