      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">I'd love it if Lancers still retained a sort of dragon &quot;theme&quot; much like how Cid or Freya worked in FF7 and FF9, respectively. IIRC, some of their abilities/equips had a dragon motif to them (Cid had the Dragoon lance, Dragon, and the awesome Dragon Dive, and Freya had Dragon Breath, Six Dragons, and Dragon's Crest).</div></div>  <br /> <br />This is mainly what I'm hoping for, not necessarily a wyvern pet. I agree, doing it up just like FFXI's dragoon would not be in good taste, but I do want some sort of dragon inspired style.  <br /> <br />I'm so curious about this AP system that the game will use to manage class abilities because it could have a big impact on what a class is. It seems, as of now, that all abilities must be equipped with AP, not just abilities learned from other jobs. I have also read that traits are equipped in the same way. This means we will have to sort of build the class according to our play style, leaving out an ability or trait some others might find essential. In other words, my Lancer may not be your lancer.  <br /> <br />That's why, to me, for SE to release quested abilities would make the most sense. It wouldn't change the class because there is no concrete notion of what the class is. If I'm playing my dragon knight lancer and in a future expansion they add some magic inspired abilities to lancer to create an elementalist type class, I can just say &quot;no thanks, I like my lancer the way it is&quot; and keep on trucking. No need for me to get offended at SE for changing my class because in reality they didn't.  <br /> <br />That's just me though. No offense to Lancer purists out there, but I would like to see the class spiced up a little while still giving us choices.      <br /> <br /></div>
