      <div class="msgContentFrame">I know where your coming from by referring to wow, I'm currently playing it right now till FFXIV comes out and pretty much the ONLY thing that's interesting and takes skill in that game is pvp. But I wasn't talking about pvp in WOW, I was talking in comparison to pvp in FFXI. I used all sorts of different sub jobs, and main job combo's that would be aweful in a party setup, yet crushed in pvp. For instance RNG/WHM, NIN/BLM, DRK/RDM, PLD/RDM, NIN/DNC, SAM/DNC with soboro, THF/DRG, SAM/BRD just to name a few. On top of that, when you mentioned the balance of the abilities....  <br />I remember when I first started playing FFXI after they &quot;fixed&quot; pvp, they totally destroyed it imo. Nerfed crits, melee damage, and ranged attacks.... Basically they made it to were any skilled caster class could EASILY have his way with pretty much any melee class. It was at least moderatly balanced before, but after that update it completey shifted the balance of control over to mages all day long. And basically made BLU unstoppable with the right spell set. A well geared blu with the right merits can two-shot just about any class within seconds. I remember before that nerf when you heard Soul Eater go off, someone was about to get one-shot with Guillotine lol. Now your lucky to pull off enough damage to get through someone's Stoneskin. Thus why DRK/RDM, or PLD/RDM is almost impossible to beat in pvp now.  <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>75SAM 75PLD 75DRK 75WAR 75NIN 75BLM 75MNK 65BLU <br /> <br />I miss you guys in Granddesign! </div></div>
