      <div class="msgContentFrame">I don't care if its a shadow of FF11 in the slightest way - with that mindset you might as well get rid of all the classes in 14 since they're basically the same classes as 11 with different names and new abilities. Shocking. I know. <br /> <br />Having a pet was incredibly unique for the class in the series and they would have to pretty foolish not to implement something similar in that regard in 14. As some mentioned above, Drg basically did have a cult status in the game with scores of people leveling it regardless of the negative thoughts on the class. Just like all these new classes, which are recycled classes from 11 with new names (as aforementioned above), they could just give it new abilities and touch upon the things people begged for in 11 for the Drg pet (IE size, color, armor, body types, class types, etc) and make it far better. <br /> <br />I for one would welcome a new DRG class that took elements from 11 and made them grander and more intuitive approach to it and your interactions/commands with it.  <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://www.countingsheep.org/" rel="external nofollow" title="www.countingsheep.org/">Counting Sheep of Fabul</a>  <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2163445" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2163445">Vackashken Zuth</a> <br /> <br /></div></div>
