      <div class="msgContentFrame">Hi. I'm cut and pasting a post I made in a different forum about this. I'd like to see what people here think. <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">I played FFXI on and off since NA launch till about a year ago. I pretty much exlusively played DRG. Nothing else was leveled past 37. <br /> <br />Initially I was disappointed with the direction they took it compared with older games, But I still really loved it. Wuffi was really awesome. <br /> <br />Like others have said, I don't think the wyvern would have any place here with the lancer and, although I've considered the idea, I also don't think an advancing class system [like FF1s] would fit into this game. <br /> <br /> <br />What I really really hope they do put in however, is a Jump attack, in the vain old FF games. <br /> <br />[ie it keeps you in the air, than lands for good damage. They didn't have this in 11. They also took it out of some more recent FF spinoff games] <br /> <br />There's no reason it shouldn't fit in. The patern I'm seeing with lancer now in FFXIV is damge plus utility in all their abilities. It could be a TP attack with whatever kind of TP cost they want to put on it, launch you into the air protecting you from attacks for a specific amount of time, than landing on the targeted enemy for high damage. It could hit as hard as other spike damage attacks from the heavy hitter classes but be balanced out with the offensive disadvantage of keeping you off the screen. Although this same function can obviously be used to your advantage in other ways, such as avoiding powerful telegraphed attacks, other AoE, or just prolonging your life for a bit if you take too much hate. <br /> <br />Nothing beats the satisfaction of waiting several seconds, than seeing your character land hard on the enemy for big damage. Imagine this scenario; your low on health, have all the hate, gonna die. You Jump. Your time in the air gives the party enough time to get the enemy to low hp, than your landing attack is just enough to finish it off. Granted, this wouldn't happen all the time,... but how awesome would it be!? <br /> <br />Another thing I'd have liked to had is Lancet. It's kind of an old dragoon staple. Although Kain didn't have it, Lancers in FFV got it, as well as Cid in FFVII and Fraya in FFIX. It's basically a single lance thrust that drains a decent amount of HP and MP with the attack. Its hard to tell if they will put that in because they already have a whole line of attacks with very similar functions in the game now. <br /> <br />hmmm rant over I guess.</div></div>  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Aug 27th 2010  1:42am by JonnyWolf </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Mikey- server Ramuh <br />I haven't payed taxes in four years! I'm not gettin busted by a ssamwich! &gt;&lt;</div></div>
